Forest Witch – that's what a stranger shouted at me minutes before I took this photo. Based on their expression I couldn't tell if they meant it positive or negative but either way it was a compliment for me 🤣 Scenarios like this happen all the time since I started dressing in a more historical, vintage inspired way and while it can be strange at times, it can certainly make a normal day much more fun and interesting 🤎🍂 

Do you have similar stories to tell? 🤣  #YourVintageSoul

Happy 1st of December ❤️ I'm so excited for Christmas this year and I would love to know what activities and traditions are important for you during this season? ✨️ 

For me it's opening a door of my advent calendar everyday, turning on the lights of our "Schwippbogen" as soon as it gets dark, baking cookies with my family while listening to Frank Sinatra and Dean Martin, visiting the Christmas market to eat roasted almonds and cuddling on the sofa while watching our favorite Christmas films – Aschenbrödel, The Holiday and Love Actually! Those traditions are very important to me and after some tough months I think we all need the coziness and comfort this time provides ❤️ 

P.S. This photo series was actually taken in Bruxelles back in August. The colors and light reminded me so much of the Christmas time so I saved it for now ✨️ #YourVintageSoul

Let me share some facts about me to introduce myself to all the lovely new people who joined me over the past few weeks 🤎 

🕊 My name is Shirin, I'm german, from Saxony and 24 years old. 

🕊 I work in online marketing and as a fashion designer. 

🕊 Daydreaming and Overthinking are my side jobs and I probably spend more time in my head than in real life. 

🕊 I still live with my parents, primarly to help with our 16 years old poodle Suri who keeps us always busy. 

🕊 I'm an introvert who needs a lot of alone time. 

🕊 I can be very socially awkward but if you know me well I can become very open and talkative. 

🕊 I'm a hypochondriac and I struggle with anxiety but I'm learning to live with it! 

🕊 People have told me that I'm an old soul and I truly feel like an old lady sometimes. 

🕊 I love so many different style decades, from the 1700s to the 1970s, I could never choose a favorite. 

🕊 My fashion icons are Audrey Hepburn, Grace Kelly, Katharine Hepburn, Marlene Dietrich and Harry Styles. 

🕊 I'm obsessed with the Beatles and Frank Sinatra. 

🕊 Old Hollywood is another obsession of mine and I can tell you the biographies and fun facts of many dead people. 

🕊 Dancing around my room at night to 70's and 80's music is my kind of work out. 

🕊 I have a younger brother and we used to learn all the Michael Jackson moves together when we were kids.

🕊 If I could only read two authors for the rest of my life it would be Jane Austen and Agatha Christie. 

🕊 I spend too much time watching films and TV Shows and I love going to the cinema alone.

🕊 Drawing was my first ever passion and it's my way of calming down. 

🕊 I'm an aesthetician and maximalist who likes to surround herself with beautiful things that inspire me. 

🕊 Bookstores, Museums and Forests are a safe space for me. 

🕊 I spent half a year working and traveling in Ireland and I dream of doing the same in the UK or Italy.

🕊 I'm not a part of the LGBTQ+ community but I'm 100% an ally! 

🕊 I'm not religious but I believe in souls. 

🕊 Last but not least, I'm very interested in psychology and humans so please tell me about yourself too 🤎 #YourVintageSoul

Our Aschenbrödel! 🤎🌰 "Three Wishes for Cinderella" (or "Drei Haselnüsse für Aschenbrödel" the german title/"Tři oříšky pro Popelku" the original czech title) has been my favorite Christmas film ever since I can remember and it's been a tradition in my family to watch it at least 3 times during December. Specifially on the 24th after Christmas Eve dinner. A lot of great memories and happy emotions are connected to this film. As a little girl I always dreamed of being like Aschenbrödel and the prince was my first little crush. So after years of thinking about it, it was about time to finally create some inspired photos in the snow!

Merry Christmas Eve my friends 🕯✨️🤎
It's a tradition for me to share a new photo with our Christmas Pyramide – a family heirloom which is connected to a lot of memories – on this special day and today is no exception. If you're new here, you can swipe left to see the other 4 years! 

No matter if you celebrate or not, I hope you have some calm and cozy days whether that is with your family, friends or alone! Despite my first excitement for this season, I had a hard time finding the Christmas spirit this year and I know this time is not the jolliest for everyone. While it can be filled with love, togetherness and warmth, it can also be a time of sadness, stress and loneliness. Especially if you have lost someone, it can be the toughest reminder that they are not with you anymore. For me it's a season of mixed emotions but I try to make the best out of it by celebrating the loved ones who are still around! I want you to know that however you experience Christmas or the end of the year, you're thought of and loved! ✨️ #YourVintageSoul

"If you take a book with you on a journey, an odd thing happens: The book begins collecting your memories. And forever after, you have only to open that book to be back where you first read it. It will all come into your mind with the very first words: the sights you saw in that place, what it smelled like, the ice cream you ate while you were reading it... yes, books are like flypaper—memories cling to the printed page better than anything else." – Inkheart, Cornelia Funke 🍂

As I've been laying sick in bed the first days of 2023, I had some time to start a new Agatha Christie novel, "Murder Is Easy", and got reminded of this moment at the sea. I was reading Agatha Christie at the time too. The thoughts of a fresh breeze and the sounds of the waves, which were unlocked through this memory, give me comfort and hope to fully recover soon. I know a lot of you have been struggling with their health too, as their seems to be a lot in the air again. I hope you can find the time to prioritize your health and feel better soon 🤎

All you need for the sock curl method:
• a brush
• a spray bottle with water
• two scrunchies or elastic bands
• two knee high socks (especially if you have long hair like me)
• and a 6-8 hour sleep 😉

This is the only curling method I use these days and it's so fast to do in the evenings. I hope this video is helpful enough and don't forget to save it (again because the old one is unavailable) ❤️

The effect snow has on my mental health is truly astonishing! There's so much beauty in the way the snow folds itself around the trees and the bushes leaves. There's a certain kind of comfortness in the sound of our feet touching the snow. It literally makes the darkness of seasonal depression within me brighter! Does it have the same effect on you? 🤍

Here are some more "poetic" words about this that came into my mind at night: 

She couldn't help but think of winter as a grey and dark season, a time that dimed her light. But as soon as the first flakes of snow touched the trees and turned everything into a white wonderland, her heart started to sing and her smile shined brighter than the world around her! #YourVintageSoul

If Holly Golightly was a witch.. 🧙🏼‍♀️
It's Witches Night in Germany today also known as Walpurgis Night, so I thought it would be the best time to reshare this witchy video 🖤
In case you don't know Walpurgis Night – originally it was the celebration of the seasons changing, just like Halloween six months prior. But in the 16th century a mass hysteria about witchcraft took its turn. People believed the witches would gather up at the Blocksberg that specific night to meet Satan, ploting mischief and evil. So the locals would protect themselves through loud noises and bonfires, burning straw men and old belongings for good luck. Nowadays it's a lighthearted celebration again where people come together at a big bonfire, eat stick bread, have some drinks and dance and sing to folksongs!

May is #MentalHealthAwarenessMonth and it has always been important for me to break the stigma 🤍 Not only because I've struggled with anxiety and depression myself but because I've seen its effects on the people around me. Being educated not only to find ways to help ourselves but also understand other humans mental health is something to prioritize! 

With all that said, let me share some important truths with you: 

• Mental Health issues have different faces. Some of them are more visible, some of them not at all. So make sure to check in on your loved ones!
• Everyone has a different experience. Only because someone else seems to have it harder doesn't mean your feelings aren't valid. They are valid and deserve to be heard!
• Healing takes time. There will always be ups and downs on the way. Sometimes even a step back. Remind yourself that you're only a human doing their best and take it easy when needed!
• Asking for help is not a failure or a weakness. It is a natural strength and nothing to be ashamed of. Don't shy away from it! 

Last but not least, if you need a source to get deeper into the topic I highly recommend @realdepressionproject (not sponsored). I've followed them for years and they have helped me a lot gaining a better understanding and feeling less alone! 

Every month should be #MentalHealthAwarenessMonth 🤍 #YourVintageSoul
